result.name: Flame - Towngas Avenue

reviews.text:
Food is OK at reasonable prices. However the service is very lousy. The whole service team is unprofessional. I ordered my rib eye for medium rare and they brought me a well done meat.Whats more,when I checked my bill with Town Gas coupons. The captain looked very unhappy asking if I really want to use my credit card to pay the remaining amount.
I would have thought that the Town Gas coupons should be welcome as well as other payments
Below average quality but above average price. Seating is not spacious enough. Feels like eating at a local chain restaurant but paying a price at the level of an authentic steakhouse. Not worth it.
Good food. Price is reasonable. And good view as well.

Food is grand, fine and delicious but you must compromise on their customer service.  Not customer first absolutely.  Even our table was reserved, they guide you to sit away from the harbour view and if you insist, they prefer you go.  No one nor tables reserved near the balcony at that time.
Great restaurants with well flow management. The eggplant roll is a reli good appetizer.  Perfect medium rare rib eye. The smoked salmon is surprisingly stunning.
